Secretary Vilsack announced that the administration is establishing climate hubs in various regions across the country in response to the changing weather patterns that will impact agriculture and forestry. The climate hubs will analyze the risk to crop and livestock production and establish strategies to mitigate the impacts of climate change. Secretary Vilsack also discussed the bipartisan farm bill that has passed Congress, highlighting the opportunities it creates for agriculture and the economy. He also addressed concerns about the cuts to the food stamp program, stating that they will work to ensure that those who lose their benefits are able to apply for assistance through other programs.